parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt tension springs can cause the seat belts to remain loose, which can lead to inadequate protection in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract or lock-up properly
the seat belts do not tighten automatically
the seat belts require manual adjustment to remove slack
the seat belts do not function correctly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause the wheels to lock, leading to a loss of control and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle slides to a stop
the vehicle feels like it has been rear-ended.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poor Syncro Design in Reverse Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor syncro design in reverse gear can cause grinding noises, leading to premature wear and potential failure of the transmission components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Oil Engine Transfer Issue in Crank Case
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil engine transfer system can cause the engine to lack sufficient oil lubrication, leading to premature wear, damage, and potentially catastrophic engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, accidents, or even engine seizure.
symptoms: Engine oil drains back into the oil pan
